<p>When people ask what makes <strong>Little Boracay in Calatagan, Batangas</strong> so special, the answer almost always comes back to one thing: the <strong>floating bamboo cottages</strong>. This guide covers everything you need to know before booking yours.</p>

<h2>What Are the Floating Cottages?</h2>
<p>The floating cottages at Little Boracay are traditional bamboo and nipa palm structures built on pontoons and anchored directly above the shallow sandbar waters. They sit low over the water — close enough to step off the edge and wade or swim in the crystal-clear sea below.</p>
<p>Unlike beach cottages on land, the floating cottages offer a completely unique perspective: surrounded by open water on all sides, with the white sandbar below you and the South China Sea horizon stretching in every direction.</p>

<h2>How to Book a Floating Cottage</h2>
<p>To book a floating cottage at Little Boracay:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/contact">Fill in our booking form</a> with your preferred date, group size, and type of visit</li>
  <li>Message us on <a href="https://facebook.com/littleboracay" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook at @littleboracay</a></li>
  <li>Check our <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a> — Standard Package ₱5,000 for up to 10 persons; Premier Package ₱8,000</li>
</ul>
<div class="callout"><p><strong>Always book in advance</strong> — especially on weekends. Floating cottages fill up fast. We recommend booking 2–3 days ahead for regular weekends and at least a week ahead for long weekends and holidays.</p></div>

<h2>What to Bring to the Floating Cottage</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Cash (PHP)</strong> — most operators don't accept cards</li>
  <li><strong>Packed food and drinks</strong> — food service on the sandbar is very limited</li>
  <li><strong>Dry bag</strong> for phone, wallet, and valuables</li>
  <li><strong>High-SPF sunscreen</strong> (reef-safe preferred)</li>
  <li><strong>Swimwear and change of clothes</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Waterproof sandals</strong></li>
  <li>Optional: snorkeling gear, waterproof camera, portable Bluetooth speaker</li>
</ul>

<h2>Pricing</h2>
<p>See our full <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a> for current rates. Standard Package starts at ₱5,000 for up to 10 persons. Premier Package at ₱8,000 for an upgraded experience. Starfish Sandbar combo tours also available — <a href="/contact">enquire for rates</a>.</p>
